  "prompt": "Will I be arrested reentering the US with a bench warrant?",
  "response": "If you have a bench warrant out for your arrest, reentering the United States could potentially lead to your arrest. A bench warrant is typically issued by a judge when a person fails to appear in court or comply with a court order. When you reenter the U.S., law enforcement may check for any outstanding warrants, and if they find one, they could detain you.\n\nIt's advisable to address the warrant before traveling. Consulting with a legal professional can help you understand your options and the best course of action.",
